📌Objective
Automate data import process
Reduce manual errors
Improve data management efficiency
Enable relationship mapping between tables
Use Dot Walking for accessing related data
⚙️ Technologies Used
ServiceNow
Import Sets
Transform Maps
Dot Walking
Excel (CSV file)
🧩 Project Workflow
1. Prepare Excel File

Created an Excel sheet with the following fields:

Name
Email
Department
Reference Field (e.g., Manager Email / Related Data)
2. Load Data into ServiceNow
Open System Import Sets → Load Data
Upload the Excel/CSV file
Create a staging table (e.g., Import Data Table)
3. Verify Imported Data
View imported data in the staging table
Use Personalize List to display required fields
4. Create Transform Map
Map staging table fields to the target table (e.g., sys_user or any table)

Field Mapping Example:

Name → name
Email → email
Department → department
5. Relationship Mapping (Reference Field)

Used script to map reference fields (e.g., manager) using email:

var ref = new GlideRecord('sys_user');
ref.addQuery('email', source.u_reference_email);
ref.query();
if (ref.next()) {
    target.manager = ref.sys_id;
}

